++++
Carp
++++

Carp is for code templates.  It cuts down on typing, so you won't get
CARP-al tunnel.  Harharhar.

Examples
========

carp --define foo=matt --define bar=robot cliscript

    Merges the template named cliscript with the definitions from the
    command-line.

    You either need to provide the path to the cliscript or it needs to
    be one of the stored templates.

carp-list
    lists stored templates

carp-store template-file
    stores a template

carp-inspect-template cliscript
    dumps out the template and lists the required keys.

Status
======

vaporware.


